1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:04,590
-Godmother. -Baby.

3
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:07,350
-I miss you so much. -I miss you too.

4
00:01:07,350 --> 00:01:07,830
Let's go.

5
00:01:07,830 --> 00:01:08,750
Where are my parents?

6
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:09,870
They went for a checkup.

7
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:10,870
Why didn't you go?

8
00:01:10,870 --> 00:01:12,590
Our department had a checkup last week.

9
00:01:12,590 --> 00:01:13,670
Everything is fine for me.

10
00:01:13,670 --> 00:01:14,870
Then I'm relieved.

11
00:01:15,070 --> 00:01:15,910
Hello, Grandma.

12
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:17,110
Hello.

13
00:01:17,590 --> 00:01:18,310
Hello.

14
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:19,830
Whatever. Let's go.

15
00:01:22,990 --> 00:01:23,789
Young man.

16
00:01:24,190 --> 00:01:25,350
You're a son-in-law, right?

17
00:01:26,310 --> 00:01:27,190
Me too.

18
00:01:28,110 --> 00:01:28,910
Life

19
00:01:28,990 --> 00:01:30,190
is hard.

20
00:01:39,350 --> 00:01:40,229
Rabbit.

21
00:01:40,229 --> 00:01:41,870
You must be tired after sitting in the car for a whole day.

22
00:01:41,870 --> 00:01:43,310
Go watch TV in the living room.

23
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:44,350
I'm not tired.

24
00:01:44,350 --> 00:01:45,950
Godmother, why do you always treat me like a child?

25
00:01:45,950 --> 00:01:47,910
I can do this. It's not a big deal.

26
00:01:48,110 --> 00:01:48,830
My baby.

27
00:01:48,830 --> 00:01:50,870
You are a child.

28
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:51,990
Mom.

29
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:53,509
Take a break.

30
00:01:53,710 --> 00:01:54,430
Let me help her.

31
00:01:56,630 --> 00:01:57,430
Okay, I'll go.

32
00:01:57,430 --> 00:01:59,229
I'll leave this place to you two.

33
00:02:02,190 --> 00:02:04,110
You'd better stand aside

34
00:02:04,110 --> 00:02:05,950
in case blood splatters on you.

35
00:02:09,550 --> 00:02:12,150
I've never seen you in that shirt.

36
00:02:14,070 --> 00:02:14,950
Which one?

37
00:02:15,270 --> 00:02:16,310
It's the one on your birthday…

38
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:19,870
I know.

39
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:22,030
Are you that kind of person

40
00:02:22,150 --> 00:02:25,150
who doesn't cherish it when they get it?

41
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:26,310
Who knows?

42
00:02:28,550 --> 00:02:29,590
I don't know.

43
00:02:30,510 --> 00:02:31,550
How about

44
00:02:32,550 --> 00:02:33,950
let me get you first?

45
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:36,990
I...

46
00:02:38,230 --> 00:02:39,950
Damn you!

47
00:02:43,070 --> 00:02:44,750
This is aired every winter and summer vacation.

48
00:02:44,990 --> 00:02:46,350
I even memorized the lines.

49
00:02:49,550 --> 00:02:50,270
Left hand or right hand?

50
00:02:52,070 --> 00:02:52,670
Right hand.

51
00:02:55,470 --> 00:02:56,390
Are you tricking me?

52
00:03:10,710 --> 00:03:12,430
Your dad and I have something to ask you.

53
00:03:17,829 --> 00:03:19,110
You mean

54
00:03:19,630 --> 00:03:20,990
you like Rabbit?

55
00:03:22,950 --> 00:03:23,550
Yes.

56
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:26,270
What kind of feelings?

57
00:03:29,110 --> 00:03:30,750
I want to raise a family with her.

58
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:32,750
Well.

59
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:34,990
Does Rabbit like you?

60
00:03:35,470 --> 00:03:36,550
Right.

61
00:03:36,829 --> 00:03:38,230
This is more important.

62
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:40,310
Probably.

63
00:03:40,550 --> 00:03:42,070
What does it mean by "probably"?

64
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:43,750
Have you confessed your love?

65
00:03:44,590 --> 00:03:45,590
Not yet.

66
00:03:46,390 --> 00:03:48,110
When are you going to confess to her?

67
00:03:48,110 --> 00:03:49,870
My daughter-in-law may run away.

68
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:52,110
He's so slow.

69
00:03:52,110 --> 00:03:53,550
I'm so worried.

70
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:55,070
Mom.

71
00:03:55,990 --> 00:03:58,990
Don't you think I'm not good enough for Xiao Tu?

72
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:01,390
Really?

73
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:03,430
It's normal.

74
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:05,270
Rabbit is so cute.

75
00:04:05,670 --> 00:04:07,270
You only bully her.

76
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:08,630
Besides,

77
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:10,350
your personality is weird

78
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:11,550
and unlikeable.

79
00:04:12,110 --> 00:04:13,150
I don't know who you take after.

80
00:04:16,230 --> 00:04:17,269
The biggest regret

81
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:18,550
for me

82
00:04:18,709 --> 00:04:20,230
is that I don't have a daughter.

83
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:21,029
So,

84
00:04:21,029 --> 00:04:23,510
I always treat Rabbit as my daughter.

85
00:04:24,030 --> 00:04:26,030
In the past, they were young,

86
00:04:26,150 --> 00:04:27,630
so I didn't think about that.

87
00:04:27,790 --> 00:04:28,830
But that day,

88
00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:30,830
when that boy came to our house for dinner.

89
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:32,830
It was Yin...

90
00:04:32,990 --> 00:04:33,750
Yin Zihan.

91
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:34,510
Yes, that was him.

92
00:04:34,990 --> 00:04:36,790
She brought a boy back.

93
00:04:36,990 --> 00:04:39,750
It felt like I'm losing her.

94
00:04:40,590 --> 00:04:41,030
Also,

95
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:42,750
I met

96
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:44,630
Yin's mother

97
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:45,830
when I went to the parent-teacher conference for Rabbit.

98
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:47,470
She looked unreliable.

99
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:50,110
I can't imagine

100
00:04:50,110 --> 00:04:51,830
Rabbit marring into their family in the future.

101
00:04:51,830 --> 00:04:52,430
Right.

102
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:53,590
Your mother is right.

103
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:56,270
If Rabbit really gets married,

104
00:04:56,870 --> 00:04:59,270
she won't come to our house often.

105
00:04:59,990 --> 00:05:01,630
I'll also feel quite lonely.

106
00:05:02,030 --> 00:05:03,790
Ling Chao, let me tell you.

107
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:06,750
You can do anything you want.

108
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:07,870
Be thick-skinned

109
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:09,150
and thoughtful.

110
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:10,350
If you can't do it,

111
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:12,790
you can even cry and make a scene.

112
00:05:13,470 --> 00:05:14,510
I don't care.

113
00:05:14,790 --> 00:05:16,910
You must marry Rabbit.

114
00:05:18,710 --> 00:05:19,630
I'll try my best.

115
00:05:20,510 --> 00:05:21,310
Go back first.

116
00:05:29,390 --> 00:05:30,470
If you need anything,

117
00:05:30,670 --> 00:05:31,870
just let us know.

118
00:05:33,550 --> 00:05:34,070
Okay.

119
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:35,310
Don't worry.

120
00:05:35,990 --> 00:05:36,990
I can do it.

121
00:05:38,030 --> 00:05:39,630
Can he really do it?

122
00:06:00,190 --> 00:06:00,870
Hello.

123
00:06:01,350 --> 00:06:01,950
Hello.

124
00:06:01,950 --> 00:06:02,590
Yin Zihan.

125
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:04,670
What time is it now?

126
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:06,510
Don't you know I'm suffering from jet lag?

127
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:07,430
It's nine o'clock.

128
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:10,470
What's the matter?

129
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:12,030
Nothing.

130
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:14,630
Please thank your mother for me.

131
00:06:15,070 --> 00:06:15,710
Good night.

132
00:06:18,150 --> 00:06:20,310
Ling Chao, are you crazy?

133
00:06:28,070 --> 00:06:29,310
You bought so many things.

134
00:06:29,310 --> 00:06:32,110
This is the special tea from Yunhai.

135
00:06:32,110 --> 00:06:33,990
The local students said it's very good.

136
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,470
Okay.

137
00:06:35,470 --> 00:06:36,310
Okay.

138
00:06:36,310 --> 00:06:38,470
This is dried fruit.

139
00:06:38,470 --> 00:06:41,070
It's a good snack while you're watching dramas.

140
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:42,790
Try it.

141
00:06:42,790 --> 00:06:45,270
And this is the sweet potato.

142
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:47,070
I've been feeling cold

143
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:50,310
around my neck lately.

144
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:53,110
Let me find something to wrap it up.

145
00:06:53,110 --> 00:06:53,870
This…

146
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:55,030
A scarf, right?

147
00:06:55,030 --> 00:06:55,909
Let me find it for you.

148
00:06:55,990 --> 00:06:56,830
A scarf.

149
00:06:56,830 --> 00:06:58,030
-Is there any? -Sure, I must have one.

150
00:06:59,270 --> 00:06:59,870
This.

151
00:07:00,750 --> 00:07:01,710
It's my first time knitting.

152
00:07:01,710 --> 00:07:03,030
I saw my classmates knitting.

153
00:07:03,030 --> 00:07:04,030
It doesn't look good.

154
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:05,790
Why did you knit?

155
00:07:05,790 --> 00:07:06,750
It's tiring.

156
00:07:06,870 --> 00:07:07,910
It's well knitted.

157
00:07:12,870 --> 00:07:13,950
This is so fashionable.

158
00:07:13,950 --> 00:07:15,030
Yes, it is.

159
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:16,110
They're designed to be ripped

160
00:07:16,110 --> 00:07:17,350
for the ones being sold in the mall.

161
00:07:17,350 --> 00:07:18,870
Yours is much better than that.

162
00:07:19,310 --> 00:07:20,030
Put it on.

163
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:22,790
Who do your classmates

164
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:23,790
knit scarfs for?

165
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,550
Their boyfriends.

166
00:07:26,510 --> 00:07:27,710
That means

167
00:07:27,790 --> 00:07:29,950
there must a lot of girls in your class who are dating.

168
00:07:30,590 --> 00:07:31,670
Yes, there are a few.

169
00:07:31,670 --> 00:07:32,990
I'm not sure about that.

170
00:07:33,470 --> 00:07:34,670
Is there any boy

171
00:07:34,670 --> 00:07:36,830
interested in our Rabbit?

172
00:07:38,670 --> 00:07:39,390
Mom.

173
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:42,270
Are you asking if I'm in a relationship?

174
00:07:42,950 --> 00:07:44,190
Can't I ask?

175
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:45,950
I'm just caring about you.

176
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:47,830
No.

177
00:07:49,470 --> 00:07:51,830
It's not that I don't want you to date, right?

178
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,550
You're in college now.

179
00:07:53,670 --> 00:07:54,830
I mean

180
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:57,150
you are likely to go back to Yidong after graduating.

181
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:59,030
If you find someone who lives too far away,

182
00:07:59,030 --> 00:08:01,270
you'll be married far away, right?

183
00:08:01,430 --> 00:08:01,910
Yes.

184
00:08:01,910 --> 00:08:02,750
You won't marry far away, right?

185
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:04,590
We don't want you to marry far away.

186
00:08:04,590 --> 00:08:05,310
Right.

187
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:06,270
That means

188
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:08,230
I can find someone from our hometown?

189
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:10,070
Yeah, it's great to date someone from the same place.

190
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:11,150
You'll know each other well.

191
00:08:15,510 --> 00:08:16,990
So you mean

192
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:19,310
you've already found someone from our hometown?

193
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:21,790
What does he look like?

194
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:22,790
Do you have a photo?

195
00:08:22,790 --> 00:08:23,310
Right.

196
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:25,950
No, I haven't.

197
00:08:38,590 --> 00:08:39,470
I've asked around.

198
00:08:39,470 --> 00:08:40,110
Later,

199
00:08:40,110 --> 00:08:41,309
Wenhui will come out

200
00:08:41,309 --> 00:08:42,429
through the staff exit at the west gate.

201
00:08:42,429 --> 00:08:43,870
We'll wait for him there then.

202
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:44,350
Okay.

203
00:08:44,350 --> 00:08:45,990
I've contacted a driver.

204
00:08:46,070 --> 00:08:47,230
Once he comes out,

205
00:08:47,230 --> 00:08:48,390
we can catch up immediately.

206
00:08:48,390 --> 00:08:49,790
Great!

207
00:08:50,550 --> 00:08:51,790
Are you

208
00:08:52,310 --> 00:08:53,870
going to follow his car?

209
00:08:54,230 --> 00:08:55,750
None of your business.

210
00:08:56,630 --> 00:08:57,750
If you like him, you can get close to him,

211
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:59,070
but don't stalk him.

212
00:08:59,190 --> 00:09:01,270
You'll only make him uncomfortable.

213
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:02,510
What do you know?

214
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:05,030
We don't simply like him.

215
00:09:05,030 --> 00:09:06,270
This is love.

216
00:09:06,350 --> 00:09:08,590
Shouldn't you care more about him if you love him?

217
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:10,910
This stage is for his fans.

218
00:09:10,910 --> 00:09:12,790
His life is for himself.

219
00:09:12,790 --> 00:09:14,670
Don't hurt him

220
00:09:14,670 --> 00:09:15,830
in the name of loving him.

221
00:09:16,470 --> 00:09:17,870
Besides, it's dangerous to follow a car.

222
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:19,110
What if an accident occurs?

223
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:20,150
Who do you think you are?

224
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:21,510
How dare you lecture us here?

225
00:09:21,510 --> 00:09:23,310
I'm also a fan of Wenhui.

226
00:09:24,590 --> 00:09:26,670
You guys look about my age.

227
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:28,630
You should be able to tell right from wrong.

228
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:30,230
Can you be a rational fan?

229
00:09:30,630 --> 00:09:31,790
It's none of your business.

230
00:09:31,790 --> 00:09:32,510
Are you crazy?

231
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:34,230
It's none of your business. Watch your mouth.

232
00:09:36,830 --> 00:09:37,870
You can't fight.

233
00:09:38,550 --> 00:09:40,510
The idol has to pay for what his fans do.

234
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:41,950
I can't let my idol suffer this

235
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:43,630
because of me.

236
00:10:28,310 --> 00:10:28,990
Are you okay?

237
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:30,350
I'm okay.

238
00:10:30,470 --> 00:10:31,990
Luckily you showed up in time.

239
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,390
Why are you here?

240
00:10:38,830 --> 00:10:40,630
I was buying glasses there.

241
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:43,150
I saw this poster.

242
00:10:43,310 --> 00:10:44,590
I knew you've been fangirling him lately.

243
00:10:44,590 --> 00:10:45,630
So I noticed it.

244
00:10:45,870 --> 00:10:47,190
I didn't expect they…

245
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:49,070
Buying glasses?

246
00:10:50,190 --> 00:10:51,230
Where are your glasses?

247
00:10:58,070 --> 00:10:59,030
I ran too fast.

248
00:11:01,070 --> 00:11:01,790
I lost it.

249
00:11:03,070 --> 00:11:03,790
It's okay.

250
00:11:03,950 --> 00:11:05,790
You look good without glasses.

251
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:08,670
You can also try contact lenses.

252
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:10,750
The one my idol endorsed.

253
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:32,750
Is it cold?

254
00:11:33,310 --> 00:11:34,310
A little.

255
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:38,550
If he says we should go back,

256
00:11:38,590 --> 00:11:39,870
I'll turn against him now.

257
00:11:57,350 --> 00:11:58,070
Hair.

258
00:12:01,630 --> 00:12:02,630
No.

259
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:04,670
I mean you're pressing my hair.

260
00:12:38,350 --> 00:12:38,990
All right.

261
00:12:40,910 --> 00:12:42,710
This darn sweetness.

262
00:12:50,830 --> 00:12:51,550
Honey.

263
00:12:51,990 --> 00:12:52,790
Come to me.

264
00:12:58,030 --> 00:12:59,350
You're so sweet.

265
00:13:26,550 --> 00:13:27,750
I've read your proposal.

266
00:13:28,190 --> 00:13:29,230
It's well written.

267
00:13:29,510 --> 00:13:30,550
Just minor changes

268
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:31,590
are needed.

269
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:32,230
Okay.

270
00:13:46,310 --> 00:13:47,150
It's okay.

271
00:13:47,430 --> 00:13:48,430
Answer it if you want.

272
00:13:55,550 --> 00:13:56,710
What is it?

273
00:13:57,150 --> 00:13:57,950
Are you still busy?

274
00:13:58,710 --> 00:13:59,790
Let's have dinner together tonight.

275
00:14:00,270 --> 00:14:02,990
Why do you always think about eating?

276
00:14:03,670 --> 00:14:05,790
I'm in a meeting. I'm busy.

277
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:08,510
Another meeting for that seminar?

278
00:14:09,150 --> 00:14:11,670
It's a psychological health seminar.

279
00:14:11,670 --> 00:14:13,350
Not a random seminar.

280
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:15,630
They did a great job last year.

281
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:17,150
This year, the Psychology Department

282
00:14:17,150 --> 00:14:18,910
got enough funds

283
00:14:18,910 --> 00:14:21,190
to co-organize with our News Department.

284
00:14:21,510 --> 00:14:23,150
I'm in charge of a handful of projects.

285
00:14:23,150 --> 00:14:24,270
I also need to train the newcomers.

286
00:14:24,270 --> 00:14:25,230
I'm busy.

287
00:14:26,150 --> 00:14:26,990
Will you gain any credits for this?

288
00:14:27,190 --> 00:14:27,910
I think so.

289
00:14:28,590 --> 00:14:30,270
After all, I'm the person in charge.

290
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:32,350
Fine.

291
00:14:32,790 --> 00:14:33,790
I forgave you.

292
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:36,030
Talk to you later.

293
00:14:36,230 --> 00:14:36,870
Bye.

